CHANGELOG.md:375:- Added depth-2 wizard end-to-end test coverage (frac-0121): `tests/test_wizard.py` now declares `depth: 2` in its module docstring and includes `WizardEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `promptclaw/wizard.py` startup wizard surface through one realistic lifecycle: `init_project(...)` scaffolds a fresh temp project; `run_startup_wizard(...)` walks the base questionnaire (project pitch, task families, success outputs), defaults the agent roster to `["codex", "claude", "gemini"]`, queues per-agent strength questions, captures routing/verification/autonomy/ambiguity/boundaries answers, and triggers the `permission_boundaries` follow-up via the `"fully autonomous"` autonomy answer; the resulting project has every expected artifact (`prompts/00-project-vision.md`, `prompts/01-agent-roles.md`, `prompts/02-routing-rules.md`, `prompts/agents/{codex,claude,gemini}.md`, `docs/STARTUP_PROFILE.md`, `docs/STARTUP_TRANSCRIPT.md`, `.promptclaw/onboarding/startup-session.md`, and `promptclaw.json`); the persisted vision contains the project pitch and approval-gate text; `load_config(...)` exposes the project description, `routing.verification_enabled=True`, `routing.ask_user_on_ambiguity=True`, the three default agents enabled with their `instruction_file` set to `prompts/agents/<slug>.md` and capabilities of `["coding", "implementation", "testing"]` / `["architecture", "specification", "verification"]` / `["docs", "synthesis", "writing"]`; the focused helpers agree with the lifecycle (`parse_agent_roster("")` returns the default roster, `looks_vague("anything")` is `True`, `mentions_any(...)` returns `True`/`False` symmetrically, `infer_capabilities(DEFAULT_AGENT_STRENGTHS["codex"], "codex")` returns `["coding", "implementation", "refactoring", "testing"]`, `lead_lane_text("coding, implementation")` returns `"code-heavy execution and implementation"`, `verification_fit_text("verification, analysis")` returns `"strong verifier candidate"`, and `sentence_or_list(...)` produces a single line for one item and a `- `-prefixed bulleted list for multiple items); the captured `output_func` blocks include the `"Startup Wizard"` banner and the `"Ready"` summary card; and a primitive diagnostic of the roster, applied config description and routing flags, per-agent capabilities and instruction files, the relative-path file list, and a focused-helper map round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_wizard_depth.py` pins the base test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method plus a machine-readable depth marker. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because `promptclaw/wizard.py` already produced the required lifecycle output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4685 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:377:- Added depth-2 voice-alias end-to-end test coverage (frac-0120): `tests/test_voice_aliases.py` now declares `depth: 2` in its module docstring and includes `VoiceAliasesEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing voice-alias surface through one runtime diagnostic path: representative alias and passthrough resolution, full alias report generation, JSON-safe summary checks, target/source and alias-chain agreement, and a diagnostic `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)` round-trip. `tests/test_test_voice_aliases_depth.py` pins the base test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method plus a machine-readable depth marker. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because `my-claw/tools/senseweave/voice_aliases.py` already produced the required lookup/report output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4682 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:379:- Added depth-2 Theramini duet end-to-end test coverage (frac-0119): `tests/test_theramini_duet.py` now declares `depth: 2` in its module docstring and includes `TheraminiDuetEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing Theramini duet surface in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/theramini_duet.py` through one realistic conversation lifecycle. The test builds an active human-gesture state, asserts `normalize_theramini_state(...)` exposes the shared listening contract (`listening`, `speaking=False`, `silence_request=False`, `human_gesture_active`, and a `conversation` payload with `phase="listening"` / `policy="turn_taking"` / `speaker="human"`), confirms `plan_duet_response(...)` for that state produces a listening `ConversationDecision` (`lead_role="theramini"`, `support_role="cypherclaw"`, `max_overlap_beats=0`) and that `should_enter_duet(...)` is `True`, then transitions through a silence-past-response-delay state with `requested_policy="call/response"` to a speaking `ConversationDecision` (`policy="call_response"`, `may_play=True`, `lead_role="cypherclaw"`, non-empty `harmonic_intervals`, `accompaniment_texture="answering_phrase"`, non-empty `response_register` and `rhythmic_sympathy`), checks focused-helper agreement (`suggest_response_key(440.0) == ("A", root>0)`, `suggest_response_register(440.0)` matches the speaking decision's `response_register`, `suggest_response_density(1.0) == "dense"`, `suggest_response_phrase(...)` returns 3-6 positive-frequency / positive-duration notes, and `calculate_wait_beats(0, 0.5) == 0`), then transitions to a long-silence solo state where `plan_duet_response(...)` returns `phase="solo"` / `duet_active=False` and `should_exit_duet(...)` is `True`, asserts `supported_partner_behaviors()` covers the documented ensemble-space behaviors, and round-trips a primitive diagnostic of the listening normalized state, the speaking and solo decision payloads via `ConversationDecision.to_dict()`, the focused helper outputs, and the supported partner behaviors through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_theramini_duet_depth.py` pins the base test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method plus a machine-readable depth marker. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the Theramini duet surface already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4679 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:381:- Added depth-2 synthesis-architecture registry end-to-end test coverage (frac-0118): `tests/test_synthesis_architecture_registry.py` now declares `depth: 2` in its module docstring and includes `SynthesisArchitectureRegistryEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing registry public surface through one realistic diagnostic lifecycle. The test builds `build_architecture_registry_report()`, converts it with `summarize_architecture_registry_report(...)`, confirms canonical architecture IDs/phases, phase winners, phase-ranked candidates, role mappings, profile macro-control/default/fallback-chain diagnostics, and production-course synthesis concepts, then round-trips a compact diagnostic through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_synthesis_architecture_registry_depth.py` pins the base test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method plus a machine-readable depth marker. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the registry report helpers already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4676 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:383:- Added depth-2 syncopation-features end-to-end test coverage (frac-0117): `tests/test_syncopation_features.py` now declares `depth: 2` in its module docstring and includes `SyncopationFeaturesEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing syncopation + polyrhythmic-cross surface across `my-claw/tools/senseweave/groove_engine.py` and `my-claw/tools/senseweave/music_tracker.py` through one realistic groove lifecycle: `_GROOVE_PROFILES["syncopated"]` and `_GROOVE_PROFILES["polyrhythmic_cross"]` resolve to registered profiles with non-zero `syncopation_intensity` and non-empty `lane_phase_offsets` (with `polyrhythm == (3, 4)` for the cross profile), `_parse_lane_phase_offsets("0,1,2,3,1")` agrees with the directly supplied `(0, 1, 2, 3, 1)` tuple, `syncopate_phrase(...)` at `intensity=1.0` deterministically inserts leading rests into a four-note melody phrase while preserving total duration and stamping `metadata["syncopated"] == "true"`, the same call at `intensity=0.6` produces at least as many melody rests as bass rests under the same RNG seed, `_quantize_phrase_to_lane(... phase_offset_rows=2)` shifts the melody first step row to row 2 while exempting the bass first step row at row 0, and a primitive diagnostic of profiles, parsed offsets, rest counts, durations, first-step rows, and `DEFAULT_LANE_PHASE_OFFSETS` round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_syncopation_features_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2, requires the named end-to-end class/method, and requires the machine-readable `depth: 2` marker. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the syncopation + polyrhythmic-cross surface already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4673 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
