CHANGELOG.md:495:- Added depth-2 constitution end-to-end test coverage (frac-0067): `tests/test_constitution.py` now ships a `ConstitutionEndToEndTests` class that drives the existing public `Constitution` API end-to-end through 30 scenario tests covering JSON rule loading and field mapping, missing/None path fallback, malformed-JSON tolerance, unknown-extension JSON fallback, regex matching, keyword matching with case-insensitive substring comparison, combined pattern + keyword rules where either path matches, phase and agent filtering (active and inactive), compound phase + agent gating, phase-agnostic rule fan-out across every phase argument, message-vs-description fallback, `hard_rules` / `soft_rules` / `rules_for_phase` filtering, and the full evaluate → `should_block` pipeline under each `EnforcementMode` (MONITOR, SOFT, FULL) including empty-violation no-block in every mode and multi-rule violations carrying the right `rule_id`, severity, and message. `tests/test_test_constitution_depth.py` pins `tests/test_constitution.py` at fractal depth >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`) and requires the end-to-end class. Existing `TestConstitutionLoading`, `TestConstitutionEvaluate`, `TestConstitutionHelpers`, and `TestShouldBlock` assertions and the production `promptclaw/coherence/constitution.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4458 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
